parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake line corrosion and failure can lead to a loss of brake fluid, causing the brake pedal to drop to the floor, and potentially resulting in a loss of vehicle control, accidents, or injuries.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Unwanted ABS activation can cause increased stopping distance, loss of vehicle control, and potentially lead to accidents or injuries.
Worn or faulty brake rotors and pads can cause reduced braking ability, leading to accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Squealing or grinding noise when braking

symptoms: Steering wheel jerks or binds randomly
steering wheel moves unrestricted too far into a turn
vehicle swerves all over the road
steering wheel shakes while applying brakes
twitching feeling in the steering column
unintended power assist to the right
extreme vibration in the steering wheel

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Brake failure can cause accidents, near-collisions, and loss of control, especially when driving at high speeds or on wet roads.
symptoms: slow hesitation when coming to a stop
